						<div class="postbody">Although I've never used EhBASIC, it did appear to be an outstanding BASIC for 6502 when I looked into it years ago.  Unfortunately the originator, Lee Davison, died unexpectedly a few years ago; but it has been kept available by others.  See it at <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://web.archive.org/web/20120913042809/http://mycorner.no-ip.org/6502/ehbasic/index.html">http://web.archive.org/web/201209130428 ... index.html</a><!-- m --> and the github pages at <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://github.com/jefftranter/6502/tree/master/asm/ehbasic">https://github.com/jefftranter/6502/tre ... sm/ehbasic</a><!-- m --> .  With the source code available, you should be able to modify it however you need to.</div>

					
